el0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10251/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10251/canvas/1/7ca9d478-6203-424b-abf0-db69bed9e454","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T17:53:36.112Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>By standing at the top of the stairs, Alma forces Reynolds to look up, almost from a subservient position. He is shot in close-up with his face dominating the frame. He thus continues to retain control and power. Alma, however, is shot with the stairs in the frame; her position in the house remains entangled with Reynolds’s demanding nature.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-10251/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:622.6634174311922,85.24512614678815,947.957282110092,909.0668004587155"}}}]}]}]}